{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"58eb5237-713a-41b9-8d68-2b901ccf62dd","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, **file compilation order matters** — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them. The `.fsproj` has `Services.fs` before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_ht1TIiJNFi7V2zAB7UoyPx","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-2a84861d75974f448f2f0f9327628fe5/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-2a84861d75974f448f2f0f9327628fe5/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"aaa7ba68-a056-435c-a755-b212af778045","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters. Files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj` file:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs` in the compilation order.\n\nThe fix is to reorder the `<Compile Include>` items so that `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":467,"requestId":"DBE3:325178:14FC3B1:1792C87:69FD340B"},"id":"d687a76c-9780-4814-9659-227dc02ce131","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:53:39.381Z","parentId":"eb1ad5d2-0144-4528-a65a-7b8de4f754b5"}
